To read an Excel file and insert its data into a database using Java and POI or any other library, you can follow these steps:

1. Read the Excel file using POI or any other library.
2. Parse the Excel file and extract the data under the specified headings (ID, IP1, IP2, USER, TKTNO) into a list or array.
3. Connect to the database using JDBC (Java Database Connectivity).
4. Create a statement and execute an INSERT query to insert the extracted data into the database.

Here's an example code snippet that demonstrates how to read an Excel file and insert its data into a database using Java and POI:
```java
import java.io.FileInputStream;
import java.io.IOException;
import java.io.InputStream;
import java.util.List;

import org.apache.poi.ss.usermodel.Cell;
import org.apache.poi.ss.usermodel.Row;
import org.apache.poi.ss.usermodel.Sheet;
import org.apache.poi.xssf.usermodel.XSSFSheet;
import org.apache.poi.xssf.usermodel.XSSFWorkbook;

import com.mysql.jdbc.Connection;
import com.mysql.jdbc.PreparedStatement;

public class ExcelToDatabase {
    public static void main(String[] args) throws IOException {
        String excelFilePath = "path/to/your/excel/file.xlsx";
        String databaseUrl = "jdbc:mysql://localhost:3306/your_database_name";
        String databaseUsername = "your_username";
        String databasePassword = "your_password";

        Connection conn = DriverManager.getConnection(databaseUrl, databaseUsername, databasePassword);
        PreparedStatement stmt = conn.prepareStatement("INSERT INTO your_table_name (ID, IP1, IP2, USER, TKTNO) VALUES (?, ?, ?, ?, ?)");

        InputStream inputStream = new FileInputStream(excelFilePath);
        XSSFWorkbook workbook = new XSSFWorkbook(inputStream);
        XSSFSheet sheet = workbook.getSheetAt(0);

        for (Row row : sheet) {
            for (Cell cell : row) {
                String id = cell.getStringCellValue();
                String ip1 = cell.getStringCellValue();
                String ip2 = cell.getStringCellValue();
                String user = cell.getStringCellValue();
                String tktno = cell.getStringCellValue();

                stmt.setString(1, id);
                stmt.setString(2, ip1);
                stmt.setString(3, ip2);
                stmt.setString(4, user);
                stmt.setString(5, tktno);

                stmt.addBatch();
            }
        }

        stmt.executeBatch();
        conn.close();
    }
}
```
Note that you need to replace the placeholders in the code with your actual database connection details, table name, and column names. Also, make sure to import the necessary libraries at the beginning of your code.
